		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />drac's night out ok I have a slrom board I cut the but I am trouble with the 
<br />wiring this says to 
<br />SLROM (mapper 1):
<br />PRG socket:
<br />Bend up pins 1, 2, 24, 30 and 31 (or cut tracks)
<br />Solder pin 2 to hole 24 (A16)
<br />Solder pin 24 to GND (OE)
<br />Solder pin 30 to hole 1 (A17)
<br />CHR socket:
<br />Bend up pins 1, 2, 22, 24, 30 and 31 (or cut tracks)
<br />Solder pin 2 to hole 24 (A16)
<br />Solder pin 22 to hole 31 (CE or CHR /A13)
<br />Solder pin 24 to hole 2 (OE or CHR /RD)
<br /> prg socket
<br />will I cut the tracks to 1,2,24,30 and 31
<br />but I cant Solder pin 2 to hole 24 (A16) because theres no hole do I 
<br />just solder it to the pin 24 or some were else
<br />same thing with pin 24 to ground and pin 30 to hole 1
<br />anybody know

		

