	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I find it much easier to wire up with those instructions rather than cutting traces. I like to make my wiring tidy but it is not entirely necessary. If you have followed those instructions closely then there should be no problem. Even if you cut traces you still need to bend up the corresponding pin to the holes you need to wire and of course desolder the hole.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


